methods.wrapWithCastIfNecessary:
A DhFormulaColumn will unbox the result of any formula that returns a boxed type (except Boolean). If the formula
 returns null, this could trigger a NullPointerException.

:param formulaString: (java.lang.String) - The formula to potentially wrap with a cast function
:return: java.lang.String

text:
When type is either a primitive type or a boxed type, dbPrimitiveType is the type used by the DB to
 represent it -- that is, Boolean for either boolean or Boolean results, but the primitive version of all other
 primitive/boxed types. For all other types (e.g. misc Objects), dbPrimitiveType is null.
